<segment id="1" parent="1001" relname="preparation">Test a Business Continuity Plan</segment>
<segment id="2" parent="1002" relname="preparation">A plan is as good as its implementation .</segment>
<segment id="3" parent="4" relname="condition">If we do not execute the plan ,</segment>
<segment id="4" parent="1003" relname="span">the very purpose of the plan is defeated .</segment>
<segment id="5" parent="1002" relname="joint">In case of a business continuity plan , there is a twist in the tale .</segment>
<segment id="6" parent="1007" relname="span">This is because a Business Continuity Plan comes into use</segment>
<segment id="7" parent="6" relname="elaboration">only when a situation calls for it .</segment>
<segment id="8" parent="1007" relname="elaboration">Otherwise , it remains a plan .</segment>
<segment id="9" parent="1009" relname="span">So , it is important to test the plan at regular intervals</segment>
<segment id="10" parent="9" relname="purpose">to make sure that it serves the purpose .</segment>
<segment id="11" parent="1011" relname="preparation">The testing is also an indication of the emergency preparedness .</segment>
<segment id="12" parent="1012" relname="preparation">Steps</segment>
<segment id="13" parent="1013" relname="joint">Study the plan thoroughly</segment>
<segment id="14" parent="1013" relname="joint">and ensure that it is updated .</segment>
<segment id="15" parent="16" relname="condition">In case you want the testing to reveal the gaps ,</segment>
<segment id="16" parent="1016" relname="span">then you may skip the above step .</segment>
<segment id="17" parent="1018" relname="span">However ,</segment>
<segment id="18" parent="19" relname="purpose">in order to get the most out of the testing exercise ,</segment>
<segment id="19" parent="1019" relname="span">it is always better to ensure that the plan is updated .</segment>
<segment id="20" parent="1021" relname="contrast">For instance , telephone numbers might have undergone a change</segment>
<segment id="21" parent="1021" relname="contrast">or there could be people movements .</segment>
<segment id="22" parent="1022" relname="span">Having updated the plan ,</segment>
<segment id="23" parent="22" relname="elaboration">the next step is to plan the testing itself .</segment>
<segment id="24" parent="1024" relname="span">Write out the clear objective of the testing plan along with details</segment>
<segment id="25" parent="1026" relname="span">about who all are required</segment>
<segment id="26" parent="25" relname="purpose">to be part of the testing exercise ,</segment>
<segment id="27" parent="1027" relname="span">what is their role , type of testing exercise</segment>
<segment id="28" parent="1028" relname="span">that you are envisaging ,</segment>
<segment id="29" parent="28" relname="elaboration">what are the expected outcomes .</segment>
<segment id="30" parent="1030" relname="preparation">Having done the above ,</segment>
<segment id="31" parent="1032" relname="condition">decide if you want to opt for a desktop exercise</segment>
<segment id="32" parent="1032" relname="contrast">( where you simulate a real life scenario in a meeting hall or a conference room )</segment>
<segment id="33" parent="1032" relname="contrast">or you would like to do it on a real time basis .</segment>
<segment id="34" parent="1034" relname="span">For the testing exercise , it is also crucial to inform all the stakeholders well in advance</segment>
<segment id="35" parent="34" relname="purpose">so that they are prepared .</segment>
<segment id="36" parent="1036" relname="span">Keep the top management team informed</segment>
<segment id="37" parent="1037" relname="span">so that employees take the testing plan with all the seriousness</segment>
<segment id="38" parent="37" relname="elaboration">that it deserves .</segment>
<segment id="39" parent="1039" relname="joint">Communicate the venue in advance along with the date</segment>
<segment id="40" parent="1039" relname="joint">and ensure that there are no last minute cancellations .</segment>
<segment id="41" parent="1041" relname="span">Testing a Business Continuity Plan is serious business</segment>
<segment id="42" parent="41" relname="elaboration">that ca n&apos;t be delegated lower down the line .</segment>
<segment id="43" parent="1040" relname="joint">Be mentally prepared for the challenges - indifferent responses , last minute cancellations etc and focus on the broader goals .</segment>
<segment id="44" parent="1044" relname="span">It is advisable to have one or two sponsors for this exercise - like the Marketing director or Operations director or HR director</segment>
<segment id="45" parent="44" relname="elaboration">who can add value and positional influence to the testing exercise .</segment>
<segment id="46" parent="1046" relname="span">Generally the duration of the testing exercise depends on a number of factors</segment>
<segment id="47" parent="46" relname="elaboration">but in general , you can have a 1-day session for a desktop testing exercise .</segment>
<segment id="48" parent="1048" relname="preparation">It is advisable to have the testing exercise off-site</segment>
<segment id="49" parent="1049" relname="preparation">but often due to cost factors and logistical constraints ,</segment>
<segment id="50" parent="1049" relname="joint">the testing is done at the relevant location .</segment>
<segment id="51" parent="1051" relname="same_unit">3-days prior to the testing date ,</segment>
<segment id="52" parent="1051" relname="same_unit">send an executive summary of the testing plan to all stake holders .</segment>
<segment id="53" parent="1053" relname="span">Have the case studies ready at hand</segment>
<segment id="54" parent="1054" relname="span">that describe the sequence of hazardous events</segment>
<segment id="55" parent="54" relname="elaboration">taking place .</segment>
<segment id="56" parent="1057" relname="condition">On the scheduled date ,</segment>
<segment id="57" parent="1057" relname="span">begin the testing</segment>
<segment id="58" parent="57" relname="means">by clarifying the objectives clearly in the opening session .</segment>
<segment id="59" parent="1059" relname="span">Explain to the audience</segment>
<segment id="60" parent="1060" relname="contrast">that this is neither a fact finding mission or a fault finding mission</segment>
<segment id="61" parent="1061" relname="span">but an attempt</segment>
<segment id="62" parent="61" relname="purpose">to ensure that the business continuity plan is fit for purpose .</segment>
<segment id="63" parent="1063" relname="span">Have one resource</segment>
<segment id="64" parent="1064" relname="span">dedicated</segment>
<segment id="65" parent="1065" relname="span">for capturing the data on a spread sheet live</segment>
<segment id="66" parent="65" relname="circumstance">when the testing is in progress .</segment>
<segment id="67" parent="1068" relname="span">Let there be one more resource</segment>
<segment id="68" parent="67" relname="elaboration">who documents the proceedings in minute details .</segment>
<segment id="69" parent="1069" relname="span">( this is not a stenographer/typist &apos;s job</segment>
<segment id="70" parent="69" relname="circumstance">as most people seem to believe ) .</segment>
<segment id="71" parent="1072" relname="attribution">Please note</segment>
<segment id="72" parent="73" relname="concession">that documentation is not only important</segment>
<segment id="73" parent="1072" relname="span">but also all minor details need to be documented .</segment>
<segment id="74" parent="1075" relname="circumstance">Following the completion of the testing plan ,</segment>
<segment id="75" parent="1075" relname="joint">it is important to give a break</segment>
<segment id="76" parent="1075" relname="joint">and request all to reassemble after 30 minutes .</segment>
<segment id="77" parent="1076" relname="sequence">During this period , capture the key lessons from the exercise .</segment>
<segment id="78" parent="1078" relname="span">Seek feedback from audience</segment>
<segment id="79" parent="78" relname="purpose">to add value to the document .</segment>
<segment id="80" parent="1081" relname="attribution">You can ask open ended questions like -</segment>
<segment id="81" parent="1082" relname="preparation">What went wrong ,</segment>
<segment id="82" parent="1082" relname="joint">what went well etc</segment>
<segment id="83" parent="1083" relname="span">and use the answers</segment>
<segment id="84" parent="83" relname="purpose">to enrich the document .</segment>
<segment id="85" parent="1084" relname="sequence">Do not run down any feedback .</segment>
<segment id="86" parent="1086" relname="preparation">In the closing session ,</segment>
<segment id="87" parent="1086" relname="sequence">thank the people for spending their time .</segment>
<segment id="88" parent="1088" relname="joint">Insist on a top management team member address the group</segment>
<segment id="89" parent="1089" relname="joint">and share their thoughts</segment>
<segment id="90" parent="1090" relname="span">and provide assurance</segment>
<segment id="91" parent="1091" relname="span">that the feedback will be used</segment>
<segment id="92" parent="91" relname="purpose">to rebuild the plan more effectively .</segment>
<segment id="93" parent="1093" relname="joint">Post testing , communicate the gaps to the group via Email</segment>
<segment id="94" parent="1094" relname="span">and also inform them</segment>
<segment id="95" parent="1095" relname="span">about how these gaps have been used</segment>
<segment id="96" parent="95" relname="purpose">to update the plan .</segment>
<segment id="97" parent="1098" relname="condition">Update the plan ,</segment>
<segment id="98" parent="1098" relname="joint">archive the earlier versions</segment>
<segment id="99" parent="1098" relname="joint">and communicate the new plan to all stakeholders with the revision number and date .</segment>
<segment id="100" parent="1100" relname="span">Do seek management feedback</segment>
<segment id="101" parent="1101" relname="joint">( You ask</segment>
<segment id="102" parent="1101" relname="joint">and you will get it ! )</segment>
<segment id="103" parent="1103" relname="span">It may be worthwhile to do a random check on the next period</segment>
<segment id="104" parent="1105" relname="span">for testing the plan</segment>
<segment id="105" parent="104" relname="elaboration">( perhaps after 6 months )</segment>
<segment id="106" parent="1104" relname="joint">and also if we can do a real time simulation .</segment>
<segment id="107" parent="1107" relname="joint">For example allow operations at a site to come to a grinding halt by way of artificially created hazard</segment>
<segment id="108" parent="1108" relname="span">and then work</segment>
<segment id="109" parent="108" relname="elaboration">at testing the plan .</segment>
<segment id="110" parent="1106" relname="joint">This will need buy-in from the top team .</segment>
